<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex">
  <title>{% block title %}Weekly Movers{% endblock %}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_root }}/assets/tabulator.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_root }}/assets/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div>
      <h1><a href="{{ asset_root }}/" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">Weekly Movers</a></h1>
      <div class="meta">as of {{ as_of }} ET · {{ universe_size }} universe · {{ screen_size }} in screen</div>
    </div>
    <nav>
      <a href="{{ asset_root }}/">Screen</a>
      <a href="{{ asset_root }}/notes/">Notes</a>
      <a href="{{ asset_root }}/about.html">About</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  {% block body %}{% endblock %}

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <details>
      <summary>How the screen works</summary>
      <div class="formulas">
Trailing 5 trading days, OR-combined inclusion. Bucket A: $300–$800 with any of:<br>
  · Range:        max(High) − min(Low) ≥ $15<br>
  · 5-day return: |Close[t] − Close[t-5]| ≥ $15<br>
  · Max daily:    max |daily ΔClose| ≥ $15<br>
Bucket B: $0.79–$20 with any of those expressed as 20% relative. Both buckets require<br>
30-day avg dollar volume ≥ $1,000,000.
      </div>
    </details>
    <p class="disclaimer">
      Not financial advice. Information only. Past performance is not indicative of future results.
      Data may be delayed or inaccurate. The screen is descriptive — it surfaces names with recent
      price variation; nothing here is a recommendation to buy, sell, or hold any security.
    </p>
    <p>Built with <a href="https://github.com/shehral/weekly-movers">weekly-movers</a> ·
       Data: Polygon.io (screen), Yahoo Finance via yfinance (charts) ·
       Charts: <a href="https://tradingview.github.io/lightweight-charts/">Lightweight Charts</a></p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
